{"TopicId":155379,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Flight to Laythe","CreatedByName":"BlazerTheAmazer","CreatedById":173185,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-21T23:25:15Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"BlazerTheAmazer","CreatedById":173185,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-21T23:25:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes anyone have a suggestion on how to make a fully operational Space Shuttle that can orbit Kerbin and go to other planets? Thank you\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"luizopiloto","CreatedById":97503,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-21T23:29:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/173185-blazertheamazer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022173185\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/173185-blazertheamazer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@BlazerTheAmazer\u003C/a\u003E, your thread was moved to a more appropriated forum section.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-21T23:47:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow closely do you want it to resemble NASA\u0027s Space Shuttle? Having the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECoT\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E be way off the centerline like that make launching a lookalike very difficult.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you don\u0027t mean a lookalike, then we need a bit more of a definition of what you are interested in building. Just any old \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E spaceplane?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wanderfound","CreatedById":112611,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-22T00:40:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222929981\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022155379\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221485041115\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173185\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022BlazerTheAmazer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, BlazerTheAmazer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes anyone have a suggestion on how to make a fully operational Space Shuttle that can orbit Kerbin and go to other planets? Thank you\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can make a NASA-style vertical launch reentry glider if you want, but they aren\u0027t good for much.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you just want to go interplanetary \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E flying, see:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/81848-kerbodyne-ssto-division-omnibus-thread/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=2926904\u0026amp;embedComment=2926904\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0026amp;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/153653-kerbodyne-planet-hopper-grand-tour-in-one-launch/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBasic tricks:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n* Wings and airbreathers to get up to 30,000m/1,500m/s.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n* Just enough oxidiser to lift the apoapsis over 70km.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n* One or two LV-N\u0027s and as much \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Liquid Fuel\u0022\u003ELF\u003C/abbr\u003E tankage as you can carry.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n* Either an \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E rig or a docking port and orbital refuelling.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n* Stable enough to handle rough-field landings.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-01-22T00:44:00Z\u0022 title=\u002201/22/2017 12:44  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 22, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Wanderfound\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AeroGav","CreatedById":152027,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-01-22T04:53:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nClosest I ever got to an interplanetary \u0022space shuttle lookalike\u0022 was this\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002220161102203158_1_zps4zg8u99j.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022564\u0022 src=\u0022http://i1144.photobucket.com/albums/o492/narostel/20161102203158_1_zps4zg8u99j.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002220161105115606_1_zps116pkekd.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022564\u0022 src=\u0022http://i1144.photobucket.com/albums/o492/narostel/20161105115606_1_zps116pkekd.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002220161106080719_1_zpsidnczkpl.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022564\u0022 src=\u0022http://i1144.photobucket.com/albums/o492/narostel/20161106080719_1_zpsidnczkpl.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/AeroGav/Columbia-IV\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/AeroGav/Columbia-IV\u003C/a\u003E,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsince I clipped Xenons into the Terriers and Sparks to make the exhaust plumes blue. \u00A0It would still need refuelling to get to Laythe though, and wouldn\u0027t take off again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis would serve you much better though,\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/AeroGav/SSTL-gavd\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/AeroGav/SSTL-gavd\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOver 4k delta V once in orbit, \u00A0and it has mining equipment\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002220170115153818_1_zpslntslp8n.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022564\u0022 src=\u0022http://i249.photobucket.com/albums/gg237/Nemulias/20170115153818_1_zpslntslp8n.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}